    "ts": "1750615273.166399",
    "client_msg_id": "de25cf6e-0464-4f79-8c6d-e040731e2134",
    "text": "Dusting off my Bitsy fork with simultaneous editing across clients. Right now I have Automerge imported and working. Except - while Bitsy is a tiny game engine, it's a massive project to refactor into ES6 modules, due to that Automerge dependency.\n\nThis week I got Bitsy's built-in icons working, and I've yanked all of the onclick bindings from inline HTML into a shim module. As I refactor out all of the global state leaks, I have discovered one actual cyclic dependency between modules. I bet I can fix this with an existing instance object.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "lcUuJ",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Dusting off my Bitsy fork with simultaneous editing across clients. Right now I have Automerge imported and working. Except - while Bitsy is a tiny game engine, it's a massive project to refactor into ES6 modules, due to that Automerge dependency.\n\nThis week I got Bitsy's built-in icons working, and I've yanked all of the onclick bindings from inline HTML into a shim module. As I refactor out all of the global state leaks, I have discovered one actual cyclic dependency between modules. I bet I can fix this with an existing instance object."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
